# Fixture FM5: Long string literals may contain raw (unescaped) newlines;
# short string literals may NOT.
#
# Hypothesis: An implementation that uses the same lexer path for short and
# long strings may either:
#   (a) accept a raw newline inside a short-quoted string (wrong: parse error);
#   (b) reject a raw newline inside a long-quoted string (wrong: valid content).
#
# This fixture contains only the VALID long-string form. An additional
# `fm5-short-string-newline-invalid.ttl` tests the error case.
#
# Expected: parse succeeds; the object is a plain literal containing
# a newline character (U+000A) between "line1" and "line2".
#
# Divergence signal: AcceptRejectSplit if one parser applies short-string
# rules inside long quotes.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.5.2; §6.3 STRING_LITERAL_LONG_QUOTE vs
#       STRING_LITERAL_QUOTE.

<http://example/s> <http://example/p> """line1
line2""" .
<http://example/s> <http://example/q> """multi
line
literal""" .
